    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-11-19T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-11-19T10:00:00-05:00" n="419"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                <head>419. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Israel</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d419fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 684A.86/11–1955. Secret. Received at 2:14 p.m. Repeated to London,
                        Paris, and Cairo.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-11-19T17:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 19, 1955—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>527.<persName corresp="#p_HCC1">Herzog</persName>, Chief American Section Foreign
                    Ministry, yesterday referred to <persName corresp="#p_BGD1">Ben
                        Gurion</persName>’s November 15 conversation with Ambassador (<gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 515<note n="2" xml:id="d419fn2">
                        <ref target="#d417">Document 417</ref>.</note>) and inquired whether Embassy
                    had received information confirming or denying <persName corresp="#p_MHM1"
                        >Macmillan</persName>’s message that Secretary was in full agreement
                        <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName>’s statement. In replying I
                    avoided any direct answer but made the following points: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>US area policy had been set forth publicly in Secretary’s August 26
                            address and President’s statement November 9.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>The Secretary in his talk with <persName corresp="#p_SM1"
                                >Sharett</persName> at Paris<note n="3" xml:id="d419fn3">See <ref
                                    target="#d359">Document 359</ref>.</note> had emphasized need
                            for Israel to give urgent consideration to sacrifices it would be
                            willing to make to obtain settlement.</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>The <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> endorses <persName
                                corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName>’s speech insofar as it supports
                            the Secretary’s August 26 address.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>In reply,<persName corresp="#p_HCC1">Herzog</persName> in a tone of unwonted
                    bitterness said that <persName corresp="#p_NNNGA1">Nasser</persName> appeared to
                    be getting everything he wanted. He was getting his arms from the Soviet Union,
                    the High Aswan Dam from the US and now <persName corresp="#p_ESA1"
                        >Eden</persName> had come along and offered him slices of Israel’s
                    territory. I commented it was not clear at this moment as to how any of these 3
                    matters were developing but suggested that perhaps Israel was too prone to look
                    to the US to solve all of its problems and that the time had arrived for <gloss
                        target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> to do some hard practical thinking re bringing
                    about an Israel-Arab settlement. It appeared to me that if there was going to be
                    a settlement an accommodation by both sides was required.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WGTD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">White</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
